76-2207.29.Fifteen-hour National Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice Course, defined.

Fifteen-hour National Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice Course means the course as approved by the Appraiser Qualifications Board.

SourceLaws 2014, LB717, § 7;R.S.Supp.,2014, § 76-2212.01;Laws 2015, LB139, § 21;Laws 2016, LB731, § 2;R.S.Supp.,2016, § 76-2207.13;Laws 2018, LB741, § 18.
